The same project that has me working with WPF has me busy on a few fronts. I've been spending the last few days writing a tool to export data out of an <a href="http://support.esri.com/index.cfm?fa=knowledgebase.gisDictionary.search&amp;searchTerm=ArcObjects">ArcObjects</a> feature class and dump it to a pgsql .sql file. <a href="http://www.esri.com/products.html">ArcGIS</a> acts as a serviceable generic data accessor to many vector data types and ArcCatalog provides a decent UI for the user community I'm targeting (also, they already have it). As a result, I've been developing an ArcCatalog command that exports a selected feature class.

As the title of this post suggests, I didn't have a lot of time in which to accomplish this task.
<!--more-->

The code makes use of a couple of <a href="http://www.codeplex.com/SharpMap">SharpMap</a> objects as well as som code from <a href="http://code.google.com/p/ziggis">zigGIS</a> in order to convert the <a href="http://www.esri.com">ESRI</a> geometry to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Well-known_text">WKT</a> and then to <a href="http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.0/en/gis-wkb-format.html">WKB</a> (formatted as a hex string) and dump it to an sql file. The C# code for the class that does all of the real work is:

using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using System.IO;
using System.Text;
using ESRI.ArcGIS.Geodatabase;
using ESRI.ArcGIS.Geometry;

namespace FeatureClassToPgSql
{
    public class PgSqlWriter
    {
        private bool _dropTable = true;
        private string _schema = "public";
        private string _table = "";
        private string _geomcol = "shape";
        private int _srid = -1;
        private string _outfile;
        private StringBuilder _sb = null;
        private IFeatureClass _fc;
        private Dictionary&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;lt;int, bool&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;gt; loadFields = new Dictionary&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;lt;int, bool&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;gt;();

        public PgSqlWriter(IFeatureClass fc, bool dropTable, string schema, string table, int srid, string outfile)
        {
            _sb = new StringBuilder();
            _fc = fc;
            _dropTable = dropTable;
            _srid = srid;
            _table = table.ToLower();
            _schema = schema;
            _outfile = outfile;
        }

        public void Export()
        {
            try
            {
                if (_dropTable)
                {
                    //add syntax for dropping table and geometry column
                    _sb.AppendLine(DropGeometryColumn());
                    _sb.AppendLine(DropTable());
                }
                else
                {
                    //add the lines commented out for later use
                    _sb.AppendLine("--" + DropGeometryColumn());
                    _sb.AppendLine("--" + DropTable());
                }
                _sb.AppendLine("BEGIN;");
                _sb.AppendLine(CreateTable());
                _sb.AppendLine(AddGeometryColumn());
                _sb.AppendLine(CreateSpatialIndex());
                _sb.AppendLine(InsertRows());
                _sb.AppendLine("END;");
                FileStream outputStream = new FileStream(_outfile, FileMode.Create);
                StreamWriter sWriter = new StreamWriter(outputStream);
                sWriter.Write(_sb.ToString());
                sWriter.Flush();
                outputStream.Close();
            }
            catch
            {
                throw;
            }
        }

        public string DropGeometryColumn()
        {
            string retval = "SELECT DropGeometryColumn('" + _schema + "','" + _table + "','" + _geomcol + "');";
            return retval;
        }

        public string DropTable()
        {
            string retval = "DROP TABLE \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",";
                        valuesClause += FormatFieldValue(fld, feat.get_Value(j)) + ",";
                    }
                }
                insertClause += _geomcol + ")" + Environment.NewLine;
                valuesClause += "'SRID=" + _srid.ToString() + ";" + ConvertToHex(feat.Shape) + "');" + Environment.NewLine;
                //valuesClause += "GeometryFromText('" + GeomHelper.aoGeomToWkt(feat.Shape, false,_srid) + "'," + _srid.ToString() + ") );" + Environment.NewLine;
                retval += insertClause + valuesClause;
                feat = curs.NextFeature();
            }
            return retval;
        }

        private string Type2SqlType(esriFieldType t)
        {
            switch (t)
            {
                case esriFieldType.esriFieldTypeSingle: return "real";
                case esriFieldType.esriFieldTypeDouble: return "double precision";
                case esriFieldType.esriFieldTypeSmallInteger: return "smallint";
                case esriFieldType.esriFieldTypeInteger: return "integer";
                case esriFieldType.esriFieldTypeOID: return "integer";
                case esriFieldType.esriFieldTypeDate: return "timestamp";
                case esriFieldType.esriFieldTypeString: return "varchar";
                case esriFieldType.esriFieldTypeXML: return "text";
                default: return "";
            }
        }

        private string EsriGeomType2PgType(esriGeometryType t)
        {
            switch (t)
            {
                case esriGeometryType.esriGeometryPoint: return "POINT";
                case esriGeometryType.esriGeometryPolygon: return "MULTIPOLYGON";
                case esriGeometryType.esriGeometryPolyline: return "MULTILINESTRING";
                default: return "";
            }
        }

        private string FormatFieldValue(IField fld, object fldValue)
        {
            esriFieldType t = fld.Type;
            switch (t)
            {
                case esriFieldType.esriFieldTypeSingle: return fldValue.ToString();
                case esriFieldType.esriFieldTypeDouble: return fldValue.ToString();
                case esriFieldType.esriFieldTypeSmallInteger: return fldValue.ToString();
                case esriFieldType.esriFieldTypeInteger: return fldValue.ToString();
                case esriFieldType.esriFieldTypeRaster: return fldValue.ToString();
                case esriFieldType.esriFieldTypeDate: return "'" + fldValue.ToString() + "'::timestamp";
                case esriFieldType.esriFieldTypeString: return "'" + fldValue.ToString().Replace("'", "''") + "'";
                case esriFieldType.esriFieldTypeXML: return "'" + fldValue.ToString() + "'";
                default: return "";
            }
        }

        //converts wkt to wkb to hex string via use of SmarpMap geometries and converters
        private string ConvertToHex(IGeometry g)
        {
            string wkt = GeomHelper.aoGeomToWkt(g, false, _srid);
            SharpMap.Geometries.Geometry sg = SharpMap.Converters.WellKnownText.GeometryFromWKT.Parse(wkt);
            byte[] b = SharpMap.Converters.WellKnownBinary.GeometryToWKB.Write(sg);
            string hex = GeomHelper.byteToHexString(b);
            return hex;
        }

    }
}

In addition, this class handles the ArcObjects to WKT conversion. It's a modified version of the one from zigGIS. You'll notice it doesn't currently handle every possible geometry type but it serves the purpose here (as well as in zigGIS).

[sourcecode language="csharp"]

using System;
using System.Text;
using System.Runtime.InteropServices;
using System.Data;
using System.Collections;
using System.Globalization;
using System.Threading;
using ESRI.ArcGIS.Geometry;
using ESRI.ArcGIS.Geodatabase;
using ESRI.ArcGIS.esriSystem;
using ESRI.ArcGIS.Carto;


namespace FeatureClassToPgSql
{
    // This class helps with various conversion tasks.
    // ArcObjects -&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;gt; WKT
    // WKT -&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;gt; ArcObjects
    // etc ...
    public class GeomHelper
    {
        /// &amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;lt;summary&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;gt;
        /// Converts byte array to hex string.
        /// &amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;lt;/summary&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;gt;
        /// &amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;lt;param name="b"&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;gt;Byte array to be converted&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;lt;/param&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;gt;
        /// &amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;lt;returns&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;gt;Hex string&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;lt;/returns&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;gt;
        static public string byteToHexString(byte[] b)
        {
            try
            {
                string hex = BitConverter.ToString(b);
                hex = hex.Replace("-", "");
                return hex;
            }
            catch
            {
                return string.Empty;
            }
        }
        static public string aoGeomToWkt(IGeometry geometry, bool includeFromTextMarkup, int srid)
        {
            if (geometry is IPoint)
                return aoPointToWkt((IPoint)geometry, includeFromTextMarkup, srid);
            else if (geometry is IPolyline)
                return aoPolylineToWkt((IPolyline)geometry, includeFromTextMarkup, srid);
            else if (geometry is IPolygon)
                return aoPolygonToWkt((IPolygon)geometry, includeFromTextMarkup, srid);
            else
                return "";
        }

        static private string xyString(double x, double y)
        {
            //local settings issue, OGC is always en-US culture
            CultureInfo OGCCultureInfo = new CultureInfo("en-US");
            StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(x.ToString(OGCCultureInfo));
            sb.Append(" ");
            sb.Append(y.ToString(OGCCultureInfo));
            return sb.ToString();
        }

        static public string aoPointToWkt(IPoint point, bool includeFromTextMarkup, int srid)
        {
            StringBuilder sb;
            if (includeFromTextMarkup)
                sb = new StringBuilder("PointFromText('POINT(");
            else
                sb = new StringBuilder("POINT(");
            sb.Append(xyString(point.X, point.Y));
            if (includeFromTextMarkup)
            {
                sb.Append(")',");
                sb.Append(srid.ToString());
            }
            sb.Append(")");
            return sb.ToString();
        }

        static public string aoPolylineToWkt(IPolyline polyline, bool includeFromTextMarkup, int srid)
        {
            StringBuilder sb = aoPolyToWtkHelper((IPointCollection)polyline, false);

            
            //if (multi)
                return (includeFromTextMarkup ? "MLineFromText('" : "") +
                    "MULTILINESTRING(" + sb.ToString() +
                    (includeFromTextMarkup ? "'," + srid.ToString() : "") +
                    ")";
           // else
            
            //return (includeFromTextMarkup ? "LineFromText('" : "") +
            //    "LINESTRING" + sb.ToString() +
            //    (includeFromTextMarkup ? "'," + srid.ToString() : ""); // +
            //    //")";
        }

        static public string aoPolygonToWkt(IPolygon polygon, bool includeFromTextMarkup, int srid)
        {
            StringBuilder sb = aoPolyToWtkHelper((IPointCollection)polygon, true);

            
            //if (multi)
                return (includeFromTextMarkup ? "MPolyFromText('" : "") +
                    "MULTIPOLYGON(" + sb.ToString() +
                    (includeFromTextMarkup ? "'," + srid.ToString() : "") +
                    ")";
            //else
            
            //return (includeFromTextMarkup ? "PolyFromText('" : "") +
            //    "POLYGON" + sb.ToString() +
            //    (includeFromTextMarkup ? "'," + srid.ToString() : ""); // +
            //    //")";
        }

        static private StringBuilder aoPolyToWtkHelper(IPointCollection points, bool isPolygon)
        {
            IEnumVertex vertices = points.EnumVertices;
            StringBuilder sbMain = new StringBuilder("(");

            IPoint p;
            IPoint firstInPart = new PointClass();
            int pIdx;
            int vIdx;
            int pIdxCurr = 0;  // The current part index.
            StringBuilder sbPart = new StringBuilder();
            while ((p = nextPoint(vertices, out pIdx, out vIdx)) != null)
            {
                // Have we gotten a new part?
                // If so, close it out.
                if (pIdx != pIdxCurr)
                {
                    // We need to close this ring if it's a polygon.
                    if (isPolygon)
                    {
                        aoPolyToWktAddPoint(sbPart, firstInPart);
                        replaceLastChar(sbPart, ')');
                    }

                    aoPolyToWktAddPart(sbMain, sbPart, isPolygon);
                    sbMain.Append(",");
                    sbPart = new StringBuilder();
                    pIdxCurr = pIdx;
                }

                aoPolyToWktAddPoint(sbPart, p);

                // Save the first point in each part to later close polygons.
                if (vIdx == 0)
                    firstInPart.PutCoords(p.X, p.Y);
            }

            // Close the last part of a polygon.
            if (isPolygon)
                aoPolyToWktAddPoint(sbPart, firstInPart);
            aoPolyToWktAddPart(sbMain, sbPart, isPolygon);

            sbMain.Append(")");

            return sbMain;
        }

        static private void aoPolyToWktAddPoint(StringBuilder part, IPoint pointToAdd)
        {
            part.Append(xyString(pointToAdd.X, pointToAdd.Y));
            part.Append(",");
        }

        static private void aoPolyToWktAddPart(StringBuilder multipart, StringBuilder partToAdd, bool isPolygon)
        {
            if (isPolygon)
            {
                replaceLastChar(partToAdd, ')');
                multipart.Append("(");
            }
            else
            {
                partToAdd.Length = partToAdd.Length - 1;
                //replaceLastChar(partToAdd, '');
            }
            
            multipart.Append(partToAdd.ToString());
        }

        static private void replaceLastChar(StringBuilder stringBuilder, char c)
        {
            stringBuilder[stringBuilder.Length - 1] = c;
        }

        static private IPoint nextPoint(IEnumVertex vertices, out int partIndex, out int vertexIndex)
        {
            IPoint p;
            vertices.Next(out p, out partIndex, out vertexIndex);
            return p;
        }

    }
}

These two classes, along with SharpMap, do all of the work. At some point, I'd like to remove the SharpMap dependency from this task but it works well right now. The ESRI geometry to WKT part works well so I may investigate a more direct means of getting to WKB (such as <a href="http://www.gdal.org/">gdal</a>).
